  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Scheduled for outpatient hip arthroscopy

          -  American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) 1-3

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Prior surgery on ipsilateral hip

          -  ASA 4-6

          -  Chronic narcotic usage over 6 months or more than the equivalent of 20mg of morphine
             per day

          -  Current or prior placement of a spinal cord stimulator or intrathecal pump for pain
             control purposes

          -  Allergy to amide local anesthetics

          -  Contraindication to regional anesthesia

          -  BMI &gt; 40

          -  Females who are pregnant or plan to get pregnant during the course of the study
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
